Reasoning: The paper discusses privacy issues in social media and proposes various protection techniques to anonymize user-generated social media data. This topic falls under several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.DB (Databases), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.SD (Software Engineering). The paper discusses graph data anonymization and de-anonymization, author identification, profile attribute disclosure, user location and privacy, and recommender systems and privacy issues, which are all relevant to these sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI and cs.CR, followed by cs.DB, cs.CY, and cs.SD.
